9. Compare and contrast for, while, and do-while loops.

for loop:
for is used at the beginning for condition check.
it is best for when number of iterations is known.
for can execute 0 times if condition fails.
syntax: for(initialization,condition,increment)

while loop:
while is used at the beginning for condition check.
it is best for when number of iterations depend on condition.
while can execute 0 times if condition fails.
syntax: while(condition)


do-while loop:
while is used at the beginning for condition check.
it is best for When at least one execution is required.
do-while can execute 1 time even if condition fails.
syntax: do{}while(condition)